1
00:00:19,167 --> 00:00:22,500
You know, Celeste is just like
a Pili nut.

2
00:00:22,567 --> 00:00:23,900
You have work hard on her.

3
00:00:23,967 --> 00:00:26,633
You have to wait for the right
time before you harvest it.

4
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:27,933
Once you harvest it,

5
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,667
you should have the patience
to crack it open.

6
00:00:29,733 --> 00:00:32,300
At first, it's hard but
when you get used to it,

7
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:35,633
you won't notice that
you're making a lot.

8
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:37,967
Celeste is just tough now

9
00:00:38,033 --> 00:00:40,367
but eventually, you can soften
her heart.

10
00:00:40,433 --> 00:00:42,900
There's nothing love can't do.

11
00:00:42,967 --> 00:00:44,667
I'm really sorry.
I can't make it tonight.

12
00:00:44,733 --> 00:00:47,100
I have an appointment
with our wedding planner.

13
00:00:47,167 --> 00:00:49,467
Can't you move that?

14
00:00:49,533 --> 00:00:51,867
I seldom invite for dinner.

15
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,433
Celeste begged me about that.

16
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:56,100
I'm really sorry, I can't.

17
00:00:56,167 --> 00:00:57,533
No need to apologize.

18
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,900
Maybe next time?

19
00:00:58,967 --> 00:01:00,500
Sure, no problem.

20
00:01:00,567 --> 00:01:01,500
I'm not allowed to use
the phone,

21
00:01:01,567 --> 00:01:02,767
not allowed to talk to someone,

22
00:01:02,833 --> 00:01:04,633
and not allowed to accept
visitors.

23
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:05,967
Am I in a labor camp?

24
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:09,733
You know, honestly,
this is not fair anymore.

25
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:13,833
Either you follow my rules
or just go to jail.

26
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:14,933
You choose.

27
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:19,300
Just talk to me once you made
a decision.

28
00:01:19,367 --> 00:01:21,267
Aren't you and Celeste okay yet?

29
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:25,433
I can't remember when was the
last time we talked properly.

30
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:27,167
She's been here for a couple
of days already.

31
00:01:27,233 --> 00:01:28,700
But she also carried her
resentment towards me

32
00:01:28,767 --> 00:01:29,900
for several years now.

33
00:01:29,967 --> 00:01:31,400
So everything is my fault.

34
00:01:31,467 --> 00:01:32,800
I had an accident,
this and that.

35
00:01:32,867 --> 00:01:34,533
She talks a lot.

36
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:37,200
She blames me for everything,
annoying.

37
00:01:37,267 --> 00:01:41,133
I wish I could just disappear
from this place.

38
00:02:15,767 --> 00:02:16,733
Celeste!

39
00:02:19,567 --> 00:02:20,967
You've crossed the line.

40
00:02:21,033 --> 00:02:22,867
I will report you.

41
00:02:25,533 --> 00:02:27,533
You are causing problems again?

42
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:28,667
You haven't changed.

43
00:02:28,733 --> 00:02:30,967
You're a troublemaker.

44
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:33,333
You are giving Ms. Vangie
a headache.

45
00:02:34,433 --> 00:02:35,433
Mikoy...

46
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:37,233
Good thing I arrived.

47
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:38,600
What if I didn't arrive?

48
00:02:38,667 --> 00:02:40,300
Even Ms. Vangie who is very kind

49
00:02:40,367 --> 00:02:41,333
is running out of patience
with you.

50
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,933
You should be ashamed.

51
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,500
Mikoy, I'm sorry.

52
00:02:45,567 --> 00:02:46,767
I don't understand...

53
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:51,467
Ms. Vangie, I'm sorry.
I'll take care of her.

54
00:02:51,533 --> 00:02:54,300
Don't push through with your
recommendation to Mayor.

55
00:02:54,367 --> 00:02:56,033
I'll talk to Mayor

56
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:58,400
so the punishment for this woman
is worse.

57
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:06,100
Ms. Vangie, don't turn me over
to Mikoy, please.

58
00:03:06,167 --> 00:03:07,233
I'm sorry.

59
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:12,767
Hey, now you will beg
after you fooled Ms. Vangie.

60
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:13,767
You shut up.

61
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:15,300
I'll take care of her.

62
00:03:16,267 --> 00:03:17,767
I'm okay.

63
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:19,733
Come.

64
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:24,000
No, I'll take care of Celeste.

65
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:26,433
You should go home.
She is my responsibility.

66
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:28,133
I'll take care of her.

67
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:30,433
No, no.
No, don't talk anymore!

68
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:31,733
She's a woman, Mikoy.

69
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,800
Don't meddle, Ms. Vangie.

70
00:03:33,867 --> 00:03:35,500
I might get mad at you.

71
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:38,500
You can go.

72
00:03:38,567 --> 00:03:39,767
Madam Vangie?

73
00:03:39,833 --> 00:03:41,167
Don't beg!

74
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,367
Sorry.

75
00:03:46,433 --> 00:03:47,567
Thank you.

76
00:03:50,233 --> 00:03:51,467
- Hurry up.
- Ouch!

77
00:03:51,533 --> 00:03:52,500
Sorry...

78
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,467
Go in!

79
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:46,533
How are you, Tiffany?

80
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:49,933
So far, Dad, I love it here
in Sorsogon.

81
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:53,300
The people are kind
and the food is great.

82
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:55,467
Good.

83
00:04:55,533 --> 00:04:58,067
Did you and your Auntie Celeste
talk already?

84
00:04:59,533 --> 00:05:01,633
I haven't talked to her yet.

85
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,300
I don't need her help anyway.

86
00:05:05,267 --> 00:05:09,367
Tiff, it wouldn't hurt
if you ask help from her

87
00:05:09,433 --> 00:05:11,400
and her family.

88
00:05:11,467 --> 00:05:16,067
They know a lot of people
in Sorsogon who can help you.

89
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:22,633
Tiffany, hello?

90
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:24,100
I can't hear you.

91
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:27,333
Yes, Dad.

92
00:05:28,533 --> 00:05:29,700
Bye.

93
00:05:40,867 --> 00:05:44,033
So, it looks like you and
your stepmom

94
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:46,967
will have a bonding moment.

95
00:05:47,933 --> 00:05:49,567
Well, I just told that to Dad

96
00:05:49,633 --> 00:05:52,400
so he won't bother me anymore
about Celeste.

97
00:05:53,567 --> 00:05:55,767
And can you please stop
calling her my stepmom?

98
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:57,833
It's disgusting, Clau.

99
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:18,200
Vivian, Aurelia?

100
00:06:18,767 --> 00:06:20,900
Tonito, we've been waiting
for you.

101
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:22,100
Hi.

102
00:06:23,033 --> 00:06:24,567
I didn't know you're coming.

103
00:06:24,633 --> 00:06:27,100
Surprise, surprise!

104
00:06:27,167 --> 00:06:30,233
Aurelia brought your
favorite bakalaw dish.

105
00:06:31,667 --> 00:06:34,567
Maybe you will not refuse me
this time.

106
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:36,400
I came here to see you.

107
00:06:36,467 --> 00:06:37,700
I'm sorry.

108
00:06:37,767 --> 00:06:39,233
I'd like to join you for lunch

109
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:41,733
but I still have to attend
to some matters.

110
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:44,833
I just came home because
I'll get some files.

111
00:06:44,900 --> 00:06:47,233
And Vivian, if you remember
we have a teleconference

112
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:48,433
with the Board.

113
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:50,633
Oh, don't worry about that.

114
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:55,900
I already rescheduled it
so we can have lunch together.

115
00:06:55,967 --> 00:06:59,833
Let's eat and let's welcome
our new shareholder.

116
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:00,867
Who?

117
00:07:00,933 --> 00:07:02,100
Me.

118
00:07:05,367 --> 00:07:06,867
I don't understand.

119
00:07:06,933 --> 00:07:10,967
Wrell, Aurelia invested
her money in our company.

120
00:07:11,667 --> 00:07:14,067
That's what I'm saying
over the phone yesterday.

121
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:16,300
That's why I invited you
for dinner.

122
00:07:16,367 --> 00:07:18,133
My small victory.

123
00:07:20,067 --> 00:07:23,333
Aurelia is now part of
our company, Tonito.

124
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,633
Welcome aboard, Aurelia.

125
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:29,967
Let's eat.

126
00:07:43,633 --> 00:07:45,733
You should do your job properly,
Celeste.

127
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,800
That's not the product
of Sorsogon.

128
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:50,233
Yes, Sir.

129
00:07:51,533 --> 00:07:53,900
You've been here for a long time
and that's only your output?

130
00:07:53,967 --> 00:07:55,800
You're so fussy.

131
00:08:00,767 --> 00:08:02,467
Sorry, Sir.

132
00:08:02,533 --> 00:08:03,567
There.

133
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:07,267
Please take a video of her.

134
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:08,600
Yes, Sir.

135
00:08:41,367 --> 00:08:43,167
Focus, Mikoy.

136
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:57,133
Just for documentation.

137
00:08:57,233 --> 00:08:58,867
I'll send this to Mayor.

138
00:09:01,667 --> 00:09:02,767
Hurry up.

139
00:09:28,267 --> 00:09:29,467
You don't have to do that,
Aurelia.

140
00:09:29,533 --> 00:09:30,800
I can manage.

141
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:35,000
I'm really happy to see you
together.

142
00:09:35,067 --> 00:09:36,967
It's only Tiffany who's missing.

143
00:09:37,033 --> 00:09:40,567
Vivian, he's already engaged.

144
00:09:40,633 --> 00:09:42,933
Maybe Celeste is not the
jealous type,

145
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,267
right, Tonito?

146
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:45,633
Not at all.

147
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:48,300
Celeste has nothing to be
jealous about.

148
00:09:48,367 --> 00:09:51,767
Tonito and I are friends,
and I'm good with it.

149
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:57,600
Well, Tiffany will be happy
to see you.

150
00:10:03,033 --> 00:10:05,267
Hi, Auntie Vivian.

151
00:10:05,333 --> 00:10:07,367
Hi, Tiff.
How are you?

152
00:10:07,433 --> 00:10:09,600
We are on our way to the
Provincial Capital Building

153
00:10:09,667 --> 00:10:14,967
to consult Provincial Tourism
about our project.

154
00:10:15,033 --> 00:10:16,867
I see.

155
00:10:16,933 --> 00:10:20,267
Guess who shared the table
with me.

156
00:10:23,067 --> 00:10:24,267
Hi, Tiff.

157
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:26,000
Bon appetit.

158
00:10:28,367 --> 00:10:29,833
Oh my gosh,
is what I'm seeing real,

159
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:32,067
or am I just dreaming?

160
00:10:32,133 --> 00:10:35,000
Hi, it's so cool.

161
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:37,467
Oh my gosh, the screen though.

162
00:10:37,533 --> 00:10:42,067
You know, Mom, Dad,
can we do this when I get back?

163
00:10:42,133 --> 00:10:44,400
We'll do this more often.

164
00:10:44,467 --> 00:10:46,200
Yes, please.

165
00:10:46,267 --> 00:10:49,367
Next time I'll invite
your Auntie Celeste also.

166
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:54,933
Okay, bye.

167
00:10:58,767 --> 00:11:02,333
Tonito, that's so cruel of you.

168
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:06,333
You saw how happy she was
when she saw you together.

169
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,267
That's it.

170
00:11:08,367 --> 00:11:11,000
That's why I don't want
to give her false hope.

171
00:11:11,067 --> 00:11:12,833
It will be hard for her.

172
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:15,000
Tonito, I understand Vivian.

173
00:11:15,067 --> 00:11:18,933
Maybe the timing of what
you said is just wrong.

174
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:22,700
I don't want to put it off now
and deal with it later.

175
00:11:22,767 --> 00:11:24,967
Because what's the point?

176
00:11:25,033 --> 00:11:28,133
Celeste and I will get married
in four months.

177
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:31,667
She needs to accept that,
even you, Vivian.

178
00:11:34,967 --> 00:11:37,833
Excuse me, I have to go.

179
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:39,800
Thank you for the food, Aurelia.

180
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:51,167
Tonito is really stubborn.

181
00:12:11,867 --> 00:12:14,067
Leo, I'll just call you later,
okay?

182
00:12:15,133 --> 00:12:16,400
Let's go.

183
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:22,833
Clau, I can't join you inside.

184
00:12:23,967 --> 00:12:25,933
Dad ruined my day again.

185
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,567
It's okay, I understand.

186
00:12:27,633 --> 00:12:29,300
I'll be the one to go
to the Tourism Office.

187
00:12:29,367 --> 00:12:31,200
Just wait for me here.

188
00:12:31,267 --> 00:12:33,500
- Okay.
- Okay, see you.

189
00:12:33,567 --> 00:12:34,967
Good luck.

190
00:12:55,467 --> 00:12:58,033
Jay R, you should deliver
the orders.

191
00:12:58,100 --> 00:12:59,067
Thank you.

192
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:11,833
Are you alone?

193
00:13:15,267 --> 00:13:17,400
Are you and your boyfriend
okay now?

194
00:13:17,933 --> 00:13:19,400
What a term.

195
00:13:19,467 --> 00:13:20,867
He is your boyfriend, right?

196
00:13:20,933 --> 00:13:23,000
What? Tell me.

197
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:30,200
Ah...

198
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:31,467
really?

199
00:13:31,533 --> 00:13:33,167
That's terrible.

200
00:13:33,233 --> 00:13:34,700
That's hard.

201
00:13:34,767 --> 00:13:38,267
What he did is terrible.

202
00:13:38,333 --> 00:13:42,133
You know, if I were you,
I might give up.

203
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,333
What the hell?

204
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:45,133
What are you talking about?

205
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,567
Just chill.

206
00:13:46,633 --> 00:13:48,967
I'm just trying
to make you laugh.

207
00:13:49,033 --> 00:13:51,100
Frowning is not allowed
here in Sorsogon.

208
00:13:51,167 --> 00:13:53,000
They'll make you into feeds
for the butanding .

209
00:13:58,900 --> 00:14:03,367
So, why are you so
emotional there?

210
00:14:03,433 --> 00:14:06,233
Should I guess or you will
tell me?

211
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:16,000
Family matters,
it's none of your business.

212
00:14:23,633 --> 00:14:24,900
Do you want?

213
00:14:25,667 --> 00:14:28,167
For you, it's free.

214
00:14:28,267 --> 00:14:30,800
Sweets for good vibes.

215
00:14:32,033 --> 00:14:34,700
You are a Pili vendor.

216
00:14:34,767 --> 00:14:37,500
I'm a COO of Pili farm owner.

217
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:39,533
It's true.

218
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:43,067
Okay, now that's funny.

219
00:14:43,133 --> 00:14:45,500
- Don't I look like one?
- No!

220
00:14:45,567 --> 00:14:47,600
I'm the COO of Pili farm.

221
00:14:50,067 --> 00:14:51,400
COO...

222
00:14:54,367 --> 00:14:56,133
oh my gosh.

223
00:14:56,933 --> 00:15:00,633
There, just laugh.

224
00:15:00,700 --> 00:15:02,633
You look ugly when you frown.

225
00:15:02,733 --> 00:15:07,600
Excuse me.
You're uglier, Mr. COO.

226
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:11,233
- Oh my God.
- You should eat that.

227
00:15:11,300 --> 00:15:14,367
Yes, of course, Mr. COO.

228
00:15:16,633 --> 00:15:18,500
Mr. COO.

229
00:15:19,733 --> 00:15:22,733
- Of a Pili farm.
- Of a Pili farm.

230
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:25,300
COO.

231
00:15:28,033 --> 00:15:30,367
Yes, I even ride a horse
on our farm.

232
00:15:30,433 --> 00:15:31,467
You know, okay.

233
00:15:31,533 --> 00:15:36,133
Okay, it's not bad to dream,
right, Mr. COO?

234
00:15:36,233 --> 00:15:37,400
Yes, of course.

235
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:41,800
Oh my, I didn't know that you
eat a lot.

236
00:15:44,167 --> 00:15:46,133
Is it my fault if
it's delicious?

237
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,133
No.

238
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,167
We made that.

239
00:15:48,233 --> 00:15:52,000
You know, I can eat this
forever.

240
00:15:54,867 --> 00:15:56,000
Wait.

241
00:15:56,400 --> 00:16:02,167
Son, where are you?

242
00:16:02,233 --> 00:16:04,433
It's my time out for my work.

243
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,267
My boss is already looking
for me.

244
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:09,233
I'll wait for your companion.

245
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:11,367
No, no, it's okay.

246
00:16:11,433 --> 00:16:13,133
You know what, I don't want
to keep you any longer.

247
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,867
- Are you sure it's okay?
- Yes.

248
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:19,033
I'll just keep in touch with you

249
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:23,267
when we want to tour Sorsogon,
Mr. COO.

250
00:16:23,333 --> 00:16:25,667
- Of a Pili farm.
- Of a Pili farm.

251
00:16:27,767 --> 00:16:29,233
Bye.

252
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:30,467
Bye, Ms. Pili.

253
00:16:30,533 --> 00:16:33,333
By the way, that's more
delicious if it's not expired.

254
00:16:34,133 --> 00:16:35,200
What?

255
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:43,833
Tiff!

256
00:16:44,767 --> 00:16:47,933
- Hey.
- Oh, was that Basti?

257
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,867
Yeah, you know what,

258
00:16:49,933 --> 00:16:52,067
I'm glad we bumped
into each other.

259
00:16:52,133 --> 00:16:54,200
My mood became a bit better.

260
00:16:54,267 --> 00:16:56,733
Yeah, you look happy.

261
00:16:57,733 --> 00:16:59,800
You know, he's okay.

262
00:17:00,933 --> 00:17:03,200
He's kind.

263
00:17:03,267 --> 00:17:06,033
Maybe we just got
on the wrong foot.

264
00:17:06,467 --> 00:17:09,400
So, how's the meeting?

265
00:17:09,467 --> 00:17:11,167
I have good news.

266
00:17:11,233 --> 00:17:12,367
- Good news?
- Yeah.

267
00:17:12,433 --> 00:17:14,233
Let's talk about it later
in the hotel.

268
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:15,467
- Okay?
- Go? Go.

269
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:18,067
I can't wait.

270
00:17:18,133 --> 00:17:19,700
I'll call my Mom.

271
00:17:20,433 --> 00:17:22,167
Oh my God, I'm so excited.

272
00:17:22,233 --> 00:17:24,200
Same, oh my gosh.

273
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,767
You have a secret.

274
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:28,900
You want to say it in the hotel.

275
00:17:58,867 --> 00:17:59,867
Hi, baby girl.

276
00:17:59,933 --> 00:18:02,533
I can't wait to see you already.

277
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,500
Are you excited?

278
00:18:04,567 --> 00:18:05,867
Very.

279
00:18:05,933 --> 00:18:07,367
Aren't you afraid?

280
00:18:07,433 --> 00:18:12,067
Don't they say that raising
a daughter makes a Dad paranoid?

281
00:18:12,133 --> 00:18:14,733
Of course, I'm sure you too.

282
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,100
Actually.

283
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:18,867
Don't worry.

284
00:18:18,933 --> 00:18:20,967
You will just give birth
to our daughter

285
00:18:21,033 --> 00:18:23,400
and I'll take care of her
until she grows up.

286
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:25,100
You said that.

287
00:18:25,167 --> 00:18:26,633
Of course.

288
00:18:26,700 --> 00:18:29,333
I'll make sure that I prioritize
her above anything else.

289
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:31,700
I'll drop everything for her
if she needs me.

290
00:18:31,767 --> 00:18:36,500
I'll tuck her in at night
until she reaches college.

291
00:18:36,567 --> 00:18:38,367
Until she doesn't want it
anymore.

292
00:18:38,433 --> 00:18:42,133
I'll be her best friend,
her confidant, her cheerleader.

293
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:46,000
I'll make sure that she will
grow up full of love.

294
00:18:47,833 --> 00:18:50,667
Baby, I'll be the best father
for you.

295
00:18:50,733 --> 00:18:54,500
And I'll make sure that I would
never break your heart.

296
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,667
Really?

297
00:19:13,267 --> 00:19:16,200
I tried my best, my child.

298
00:19:16,267 --> 00:19:17,767
But I still messed up.

299
00:19:21,067 --> 00:19:23,600
I'm sorry for always
breaking your heart.

300
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:40,367
You're the only one
who can discipline her.

301
00:19:40,433 --> 00:19:43,100
I told you I'll take care
of Celeste.

302
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:46,433
Thank you so much for
substituting for me.

303
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:49,267
Take care.

304
00:19:49,333 --> 00:19:53,233
Mikoy, don't hurt her.

305
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:55,233
If she behaves, right?

306
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:58,133
Okay, take care.

307
00:19:59,933 --> 00:20:01,100
Boys.

308
00:20:07,967 --> 00:20:10,700
She's terrible,
she's exaggerated.

309
00:20:10,767 --> 00:20:12,100
She's too much.

310
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:15,400
Thank you for saving me today.

311
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:19,233
Thank you?
There's a payment for that.

312
00:20:19,300 --> 00:20:20,533
What do you mean by payment?

313
00:20:23,933 --> 00:20:25,667
My God.

314
00:20:25,733 --> 00:20:26,733
What's with you, Mikoy?

315
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:27,933
That's irritating.

316
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:31,367
Don't be like that.
I'm getting married.

317
00:20:31,433 --> 00:20:32,900
So?

318
00:20:32,967 --> 00:20:34,867
What do you mean so?

319
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:38,567
Mikoy, you're not funny.

320
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:40,967
What do you think of me?

321
00:20:41,033 --> 00:20:42,700
You know, you're dirty-minded.

322
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:47,333
Anyway, where will you take me?

323
00:20:47,733 --> 00:20:49,400
Secret.

324
00:20:49,467 --> 00:20:50,600
Don't talk like that.

325
00:20:50,667 --> 00:20:52,200
That's irritating.

326
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:57,333
I'll take care of you.

327
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:58,333
Do you trust me?

328
00:20:58,400 --> 00:20:59,367
No.

329
00:21:05,533 --> 00:21:07,433
We'll leave when this starts.

330
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,333
Are you ready?

331
00:21:15,867 --> 00:21:17,600
Let's go.

332
00:21:17,667 --> 00:21:19,567
Why do you talk like that?

333
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:35,167
Stop.

334
00:21:35,233 --> 00:21:36,500
Yep.

335
00:21:38,367 --> 00:21:40,100
Grandma Ikay!

336
00:21:42,033 --> 00:21:45,233
Celeste, is that you?

337
00:21:46,267 --> 00:21:49,267
Look at you.

338
00:21:49,333 --> 00:21:50,133
You're so beautiful.

339
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,500
Let me see.

340
00:21:52,267 --> 00:21:54,100
I missed you, Grandma Ikay.

341
00:21:54,167 --> 00:21:56,767
Me too, I missed you.

342
00:21:57,567 --> 00:21:59,233
Let's go upstairs.

343
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:00,767
Come on, let's go upstairs.

344
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:01,867
Come on.

345
00:22:08,433 --> 00:22:10,900
Come in.

346
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:14,867
- Have a seat.
- Wow, it's like a fiesta.

347
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:20,267
Grandma has been asking me
to bring you over for days now.

348
00:22:20,333 --> 00:22:23,067
Good thing you decided
to come home.

349
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:27,333
Maybe your father is very happy
to see you, right?

350
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:30,000
Let's eat.
I'm already hungry.

351
00:22:30,067 --> 00:22:31,300
Okay.

352
00:22:31,367 --> 00:22:34,600
You are still very beautiful,
Celeste.

353
00:22:35,167 --> 00:22:36,567
What's with you, Grandma?

354
00:22:36,633 --> 00:22:39,300
You are beautiful
and it doesn't fade.

355
00:22:39,367 --> 00:22:40,300
Don't say it loud.

356
00:22:40,367 --> 00:22:43,167
The neighbors might hear it.

357
00:22:43,233 --> 00:22:46,933
How is your life in Manila?

358
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:49,067
It's okay. It's happy.

359
00:22:50,567 --> 00:22:52,167
I'm getting married.

360
00:22:53,633 --> 00:22:55,967
I met him in Manila.

361
00:22:56,033 --> 00:22:59,467
You and Mikoy are invited.

362
00:22:59,533 --> 00:23:03,400
Yes, I heard about your wedding.

363
00:23:03,467 --> 00:23:07,900
Ever since you arrived,
Mikoy always talked about you.

364
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:11,200
I'm not saying anything,
Grandma.

365
00:23:13,067 --> 00:23:15,900
I'm sure everything he says
is all negative.

366
00:23:17,167 --> 00:23:19,067
Why? Is there something
positive?

367
00:23:20,267 --> 00:23:21,667
He's very grouchy.

368
00:23:21,767 --> 00:23:24,367
I'm just matching your
grouchiness.

369
00:23:31,167 --> 00:23:33,867
Hey, is that pinangat ?

370
00:23:33,933 --> 00:23:35,267
Of course.

371
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:36,467
Wow.

372
00:23:36,533 --> 00:23:39,567
I add more chilies to it

373
00:23:39,633 --> 00:23:42,633
because I know that spicy
pinangat is your favorite.

374
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:44,467
That's great.

375
00:23:44,533 --> 00:23:46,533
Grandma, she doesn't eat
spicy food anymore.

376
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:48,100
She's no longer a Sorsoguenon .

377
00:23:48,167 --> 00:23:49,733
Why?

378
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:51,367
It's not that.

379
00:23:51,433 --> 00:23:53,000
It's not that I don't like it.

380
00:23:53,067 --> 00:23:55,233
I have hyperacidity.

381
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:57,433
I'm not allowed to eat
spicy food.

382
00:23:57,533 --> 00:24:00,267
But for you, I'll eat.

383
00:24:00,333 --> 00:24:01,367
Oh.

384
00:24:01,833 --> 00:24:03,467
You can't eat spicy food
anymore.

385
00:24:04,633 --> 00:24:06,000
I can.

386
00:24:06,967 --> 00:24:08,100
Go ahead.

387
00:24:08,167 --> 00:24:09,700
- Do you want?
- Yes.

388
00:24:09,767 --> 00:24:14,333
Okay, I'll eat this but you
should eat ten chilies.

389
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:16,633
- Just ten?
- Yes.

390
00:24:16,700 --> 00:24:17,867
Call.

391
00:24:18,933 --> 00:24:20,333
- Game?
- Game.

392
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:35,033
Eat some more.

393
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:37,333
- It's ten, remember?
- Ten?

394
00:24:39,033 --> 00:24:40,100
Me also.

395
00:24:40,167 --> 00:24:41,833
You will also eat chili.

396
00:25:03,833 --> 00:25:05,233
Are we on the same page?

397
00:25:05,300 --> 00:25:07,233
- What do you mean?
- The signs are clear.

398
00:25:07,300 --> 00:25:08,567
Aurelia wants you back.

399
00:25:08,633 --> 00:25:09,600
Thank you, Mikoy.

400
00:25:09,667 --> 00:25:12,967
I forgot how happy it is here
in Sorsogon.

401
00:25:13,033 --> 00:25:16,633
You reminded me of all of that
in such a short amount of time.

402
00:25:16,700 --> 00:25:18,833
Celeste is also family now.

403
00:25:18,900 --> 00:25:21,200
Not unless I accept her
as your wife

404
00:25:21,267 --> 00:25:23,000
which will never happen.

405
00:25:23,067 --> 00:25:25,800
I have no doubts that Celeste
is quite material,

406
00:25:25,867 --> 00:25:28,033
but is she also
a mother material?

407
00:25:28,100 --> 00:25:29,733
Can she be a mother to Tiffany?

408
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:31,667
It's hard to raise a child.

409
00:25:31,733 --> 00:25:33,333
What more if it's not from you.

410
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:35,633
Because of what I saw today,
you did me a favor.

411
00:25:35,733 --> 00:25:39,467
You really proved that
I can't depend on you.

412
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:42,000
We avoid strangers.

413
00:25:42,067 --> 00:25:44,367
Our place will be disrespected.

414
00:25:44,433 --> 00:25:47,000
Only the locals can do
business here.

415
00:25:47,067 --> 00:25:48,833
I'm really from here.

416
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:50,967
Basti is my boyfriend.

417
00:25:51,033 --> 00:25:53,867
It's her mother Lucinda's
death anniversary.

418
00:25:53,933 --> 00:25:55,567
Why did you not accompany her?

419
00:25:55,633 --> 00:25:57,733
That's not my job.
That's the job of her fiancé.

420
00:25:57,800 --> 00:25:59,100
He's not here.

421
00:25:59,167 --> 00:26:00,933
What's happening with Celeste?

422
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:02,667
I've been trying to reach her
earlier.

423
00:26:02,733 --> 00:26:04,967
I can't seem to get through.

424
00:26:05,033 --> 00:26:06,033
Me too, Sir.

425
00:26:06,100 --> 00:26:07,367
I've been trying to call her
several times

426
00:26:07,433 --> 00:26:09,767
but she's been out of range.

427
00:26:09,867 --> 00:26:10,933
Why would she do that?

428
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:12,067
Our difference is,

429
00:26:12,133 --> 00:26:15,600
I'm willing to give a second
chance to the person

430
00:26:15,667 --> 00:26:16,733
who hurt me.

431
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:19,267
You should learn to give
second chances

432
00:26:19,333 --> 00:26:20,900
because if you won't give that,

433
00:26:20,967 --> 00:26:23,033
all the people in the world
would be fighting.

434
00:26:23,100 --> 00:26:25,300
It's just the two of you
together?

435
00:26:25,367 --> 00:26:27,000
Nothing happened?

436
00:26:27,067 --> 00:26:29,067
Grandma, sometimes I want
to think that you are also rude.

437
00:26:29,133 --> 00:26:32,533
I'm already old and you think
badly of me.

438
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:34,733
I apologize for being rude.

439
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:37,433
But if you're trying to attempt
to get my sympathy,

440
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:41,700
I feel so sorry for you because
my loyalty is with my Mom.
